# Production Deployment

Efemer runs on **curios-vm** — the same GCP VM as aukce.jabli.cz.

## Server

| Item | Value |
|------|-------|
| VM | `curios-vm` |
| GCP project (VM) | `aukce-496911` |
| Zone | `europe-west3-c` |
| IP | `34.179.230.234` |
| SSH user | `jan` |
| SSH key | `~/.ssh/google_compute_engine` |
| Remote app dir | `/home/jan/efemer` |
| Docker nginx port | `127.0.0.1:52184` |

## Hostname & proxy

- **Production URL**: https://efemer.jabli.cz
- Host **Caddy** (`/etc/caddy/Caddyfile`) proxies to loopback:

```
efemer.jabli.cz {
	reverse_proxy 127.0.0.1:52184
}
```

Reload after changes: `sudo caddy validate --config /etc/caddy/Caddyfile && sudo systemctl reload caddy`

## DNS

`efemer.jabli.cz` must point to **34.179.230.234** (A record). A CNAME to `jabli.cz` breaks TLS (Let's Encrypt hits the wrong IP).

## GCS (files)

- GCP project: `efemer-456414` (see `gcloud-project.mdc`)
- Bucket: `efemer-files`
- Credentials: `.secret/` (gitignored, rsynced on deploy)

## Deploy

```bash
./deploy.sh
```

`deploy.sh` builds webpack assets, rsyncs the app (excluding `.env`, `vendor`, `data/mysql`), syncs `.secret/`, then runs `deploy/remote-setup.sh` on the server.

## Server `.env`

Not synced from local. On first setup, create `~/efemer/.env` from `deploy/env.production.example` plus:

- `ENCRYPTION_KEY`, `ENCRYPTION_SALT`
- `MYSQL_PASSWORD`, `MYSQL_ROOT_PASSWORD`

Set `APP_HOST=efemer.jabli.cz`, `APP_ENV=PRODUCTION`, `APP_SCHEMA=https`, `MYSQL_HOST=mysql`.

## Remote setup

`deploy/remote-setup.sh` on the server:

```bash
# Rebuilds PHP image only when docker/php/ changes (hash in .deploy/php-image.context-sha256)
docker compose -f docker-compose.production.yml build php   # conditional
docker compose -f docker-compose.production.yml up -d --no-build
docker compose -f docker-compose.production.yml exec -T php composer install --no-dev --optimize-autoloader --no-interaction
docker compose -f docker-compose.production.yml exec -T php php bin/migrate.php
```

`vendor/` is installed in the PHP container on the server — the image includes Composer.

## Composer

Run Composer **inside the PHP container**, not on the host (use host UID so `vendor/` stays owned by you):

```bash
docker compose exec -T -u "$(id -u):$(id -g)" php composer update
docker compose exec -T -u "$(id -u):$(id -g)" php composer require vendor/package
docker compose exec -T -u "$(id -u):$(id -g)" php composer install
```

Production deploy runs `composer install --no-dev` via `remote-setup.sh` after containers start.

## Migrations on production

After deploy, migrations run automatically via `remote-setup.sh`. To run manually:

```bash
docker compose -f docker-compose.production.yml exec -T php php bin/migrate.php
```

## Gotchas

- If `~/efemer/vendor` is owned by root (from an old `docker compose run`), fix before rsync: `sudo rm -rf vendor && mkdir vendor && chown jan:jan vendor`
- `aukce` uses port `54184`, `movies` uses `50184` — efemer uses `52184`
- Run migrations locally after schema changes (see `migrations.mdc`), then deploy

## Post-deploy verification

After every deploy, confirm the site responds before finishing:

```bash
curl -sI -o /dev/null -w '%{http_code}' https://efemer.jabli.cz/admin   # expect 302
```

If down, investigate (containers, logs, `.env`, vendor permissions) and fix until `/admin` returns `302` again. See `.cursor/skills/deploy/SKILL.md`.
